<planning_instructions>
Develop an attack strategy considering the following:

1. **Reconnaissance Phase** (budget: {{.ReconMinutes}} minutes)
   - Identify attack surface: ports, services, technologies
   - Map application structure and entry points
   - Gather intelligence about the target environment

2. **Attack Phase** (budget: {{.AttackMinutes}} minutes per vector)
   - Prioritize attack vectors based on reconnaissance findings
   - Each vector gets its own time budget — if it stalls, the system will auto-pivot
   - After {{.FailureLimit}} consecutive failures on any vector, you will be redirected to the next

3. **Post-Exploitation Phase** (budget: {{.PostExploitMinutes}} minutes)
   - Leverage any successful exploits for deeper access
   - Document findings and evidence
   - Identify additional attack paths from compromised positions

**Key Principle:** Do not rabbit-hole on a single approach. The budget system will enforce pivots, but proactively switching approaches when progress stalls will yield better results.

Plan your attack vectors in priority order so that when one is exhausted, the next one is ready.
</planning_instructions>
